comment.undefined: A parameter variable is a WINGS workflow class that represents a description of an input parameter of a workflow step.
The WINGS output link is a WINGS workflow class that has an origin node and a variable.
The WINGS inout link is a WINGS workflow class that has an origin node, a destination node and a variable.
The WINGS input link is a WINGS workflow class that has a destination node and a variable.
The WINGS ComponentVariable is a WINGS workflow class that represents a component variable in the workflow specification.
The WINGS data variable is a WINGS workflow class that represents a workflow template artifact in OPMW and is a variable in the WINGS template specification.
The WINGS WorkflowInstance is a class in the WINGS Ontology that represents the workflow instance that is connected to a workflow execution file by the relation hasPlan workflowInstance.
The WINGS workflow is a class in the WINGS Ontology that represents the entire workflow created in the WINGS workflow system.
The WINGS workflow template is a class in the WINGS Ontology that represents the entire workflow template created in the WINGS workflow system.
The WINGS MetaData is a WINGS workflow class that represents the metadata pertaining to a template specification.
The WINGS Node is a WINGS workflow class that represents a node in the template specification. The node has components in templates.
The WINGS ComponentSetRule is a WINGS workflow class that represents a set of component rules in the workflow specification.
The WINGS Link is a WINGS workflow class that represents a link in the template specification.
The WINGS hasVersion is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflow has a version number.
The WINGS hasOriginNode is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow Link and Node i.e. a WingsWorkflowLink hasOriginNode a WingsWorkflowNode.
The WINGS hasRules is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflow has a set of rules (specified as strings).
The WINGS isConcrete is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflow Component Variable is abstract or concrete.

The WINGS hasComponent is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow Node and a Component Variable i.e. a WingsWorkflowNode hasComponent a WingsWorkflowComponentVariable.

The WINGS hasPortSetCreationRule is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowNode and SetCreationRule i.e. a WingsWorkflowNode hasPortSetCreationRule WingsWorkflowSetCreationRule.
The WINGS hasContributor is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflow has a contributor (specified as a string).
The WINGS hasInputRole is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow SetCreationExpression and Port.

The WINGS hasComponentSetCreationRule is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowNode and a SetCreationRule i.e. a WingsWorkflowNode hasComponentSetCreationRule SetCreationRule.
The WINGS satisfiesRole is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowPort and WingsWorkflowRole i.e. a WingsWorkflowPort satisfiesRole WingsWorkflowRole.
The WINGS hasInputPort is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowNode and Port i.e. a WingsWorkflowNode hasInputPort WingsWorkflowPort.
The WINGS createdFrom is a WINGS workflow data property that represents the WingsWorkflowMetaData has createdFrom as a property.
The WINGS hasExpressionArgument is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a SetCreationExpressio and Port.
The WINGS isInactive is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflow is active or not.
The WINGS hasDocumentation is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflow metadata contains documentation for the workflow.
The WINGS breakPoint is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflowVariable always has a breakpoint.
The WINGS hasWorkflow is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow Node and WingsWorkflow i.e. a WingsWorkflowNode hasWorkflow WingsWorkflow.
The WINGS createWorkflowSets is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflowSetCreationRule has the ability to createWorkflowSets.

The WINGS createSetsOn is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow SetCreationRule and a Component Variable i.e. a WingsWorkflowNode createSetsOn a WingsWorkflowComponentVariable.
The WINGS hasDestinationNode is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow Link and Node i.e. a WingsWorkflowLink hasDestinationNode a WingsWorkflowNode.
The WINGS hasParameterValue is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflow parameter variable has a parameter value.
The WINGS createComponentSets is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflowSetCreationRule has the ability to createComponentSets.

The WINGS mapsToVariable is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow Role and WingsWorkflowVariable i.e. a WingsWorkflowNRole mapsToVariable WingsWorkflowVariable.
The WINGS hasOriginPort is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowLink and Port i.e. a WingsWorkflowLink hasOriginPort WingsWorkflowPort.
The WINGS tellmeData is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflowMetadata has a property for knowing the data (specifying the data as a set of strings).

example.value:
@prefix workflow: <http://www.wings-workflows.org/ontology/workflow.owl#> .

        <http://ontosoft.isi.edu:8080/wings-portal/export/users/tirth/TestingDomain/workflows/s6.owl#third_node_comp>
            workflow:hasComponentBinding 
              <http://ontosoft.isi.edu:8080/wings-portal/export/users/tirth/TestingDomain/components/
              library.owl#third> ;
            workflow:isConcrete 
              true .

comment.undefined: The WINGS hasComponentBinding is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowComponentVariable and a ComponentBinding i.e. a WingsWorkflowComponentVariable hasComponentBinding WingsWorkflowComponentBinding.
The WINGS hasVariable is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow Link and Variable i.e. a WingsWorkflowLink hasVariable a WingsWorkflowVariable.
The WINGS autoFill is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflowParameterVariable is autoFillable or not (specified as a boolean).
The WINGS hasMetadata is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow and MetaData i.e. a WingsWorkflow hasMetadata WingsWorkflowMetaData.
The WINGS hasOutputPort is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowNode and Port i.e. a WingsWorkflowNode hasOutputPort WingsWorkflowPort.
The WINGS hasOutputRole is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow and Role i.e. a WingsWorkflow hasOutputRole WingsWorkflowRole.

example.value:
@prefix workflow: <http://www.wings-workflows.org/ontology/workflow.owl#> .

           <http://ontosoft.isi.edu:8080/wings-portal/export/users/
           tirth/TestingDomain/workflows/r1.owl#xmltotext_node_InputFormattedFile_role>
              workflow:hasRoleID 
                "InputFormattedFile"^^xsd:string ;
              workflow:hasDimensionality 
                0 .

comment.undefined: The WINGS hasRoleID is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflowRole has a role id.
The WINGS hasDestinationPort is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowLink and Port i.e. a WingsWorkflowLink hasDestinationPort WingsWorkflowPort.
The WINGS hasDimensionality is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflow Input is a collection or not (specified as a number(int)).
The WINGS hasNode is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow and Node i.e. a WingsWorkflow hasNode WingsWorkflowNode.
The WINGS lastUpdateTime is a WINGS workflow data property that represents a WingsWorkflow has a last updated time(the range being a dateTime).
The WINGS hasLink is a WINGS workflow object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflow and Link i.e. a WingsWorkflow hasLink WingsWorkflowLink.
